column5: http://www.cbc.ca/m/news/canada/ottawa/topstories/ice-safety-warnings-issued-after-1-fatality-2-close-calls-1.2881093  Be careful out there folks  G
Sheesh!! Theres no learnin for some. Crappy way to grab a headline.
Just got back from checking the cottage on Pigeon Lake. Froze over with flat ice. A guy out there ice sailing.  Gannon Narrows wide open
How's it looking North of Honey harbour on smaller lakes? I was thinking of doing some recon in Huntsville and the like tomorrow but if it's risky I'll just stay home sharpening my hooks.
Probably not a good idea given the forecast for the next few days.
Lots of ice up here Jeremy.  This rain will knock off the snow and make for great ice conditions once things firm up.  Sledding...not so much
Thanks Joey. In the new year, let me know if you and Chad are free and need a third to explore a lake. It seems like forever since I've seen you gents.
